13 WHEREAS, National Firefighters' Day is observed annually on May
14 4 to honor the sacrifices and dedication of firefighters across the
15 nation, who risk their lives to protect communities and save lives
16 from the devastation of fire and other emergencies; and
17 WHEREAS, firefighters demonstrate unwavering courage,
18 selflessness, and resilience in the face of danger, exemplifying the
19 highest ideals of service to others and commitment to public safety;
20 and
21 WHEREAS, Fire Departments in Oklahoma play a vital role in
22 safeguarding the residents, visitors, and properties of Oklahoma
23 responding to emergencies with professionalism, skill, and
24 compassion; and
